<div class="prose">

<p>The AP article you just read is a news story ABOUT a report. This page is selected points from the report itself — the United Nations University Institute for Water, Environment and Health (UNU-INWEH), June 2026. Same facts, different source type. Notice what changes.</p>

<h2>The numbers AP reported — straight from the source</h2>

<ul>
  <li>In 2025, global data centers consumed an estimated 448 TWh of electricity. If data centers were a country, they would rank 11th in the world by electricity consumption. (p. 10)</li>
  <li>That electricity carried a carbon footprint of 189 million tonnes of CO₂e — offsetting it would take 3.2 billion tree seedlings grown for 10 years, roughly every tree in the United Kingdom. (p. 10)</li>
  <li>The water footprint: 4.5 trillion liters — 1.8 million Olympic-sized pools, or the annual basic domestic water needs of over 600 million people in Sub-Saharan Africa. (p. 10)</li>
  <li>AI accounted for roughly 20% of data centers' electricity in 2025, projected to reach 40% by 2030. (p. 10)</li>
  <li>Projected 2030 consumption: over 945 TWh — nearly 3% of global electricity, ranking 6th if it were a country. (p. 10)</li>
</ul>

